cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SY

The paper proposes a shipboard Collision-At-Sea avoidance system based on video image processing, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The system also uses a convolutional neural network, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the potential security risks associated with maritime collisions, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
